---
import { C, FONT } from "../infographicTokens";
---

<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 720 320" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
  <title>Where the heat constants come from</title>
  <desc>The 1.08, 0.68, and 4.5 constants are derived from standard air density, specific heat, latent heat of vaporization, and minutes per hour.</desc>

  <text x="360" y="32" text-anchor="middle" fill={C.dark} font-family={FONT} font-size="16" font-weight="700">Where the constants come from</text>

  <!-- 1.08 -->
  <rect x="60" y="52" width="600" height="64" rx="10" fill={C.blueLight} stroke={C.blue} stroke-width="1.5" />
  <text x="84" y="80" fill={C.blue} font-family={FONT} font-size="18" font-weight="800">1.08</text>
  <text x="150" y="80" fill={C.dark} font-family={FONT} font-size="13" font-weight="700">0.24 (specific heat, BTU/lb&#183;&#176;F) &#215; 60 (min/hr) &#215; 0.075 (density, lb/ft&#179;)</text>
  <text x="150" y="102" fill={C.muted} font-family={FONT} font-size="11">Used for sensible (temperature) heat.</text>

  <!-- 0.68 -->
  <rect x="60" y="124" width="600" height="78" rx="10" fill={C.primaryLight} stroke={C.primary} stroke-width="1.5" />
  <text x="84" y="152" fill={C.primary} font-family={FONT} font-size="18" font-weight="800">0.68</text>
  <text x="150" y="148" fill={C.dark} font-family={FONT} font-size="13" font-weight="700">0.075 &#215; 60 &#215; 1,061 (latent heat, BTU/lb)</text>
  <text x="150" y="168" fill={C.dark} font-family={FONT} font-size="13" font-weight="700">&#247; 7,000 (grains/lb)</text>
  <text x="150" y="190" fill={C.muted} font-family={FONT} font-size="11">Used for latent (moisture) heat per grain difference.</text>

  <!-- 4.5 -->
  <rect x="60" y="210" width="600" height="64" rx="10" fill={C.panelBg} stroke={C.border} stroke-width="1.5" />
  <text x="84" y="238" fill={C.dark} font-family={FONT} font-size="18" font-weight="800">4.5</text>
  <text x="150" y="238" fill={C.dark} font-family={FONT} font-size="13" font-weight="700">60 (min/hr) &#215; 0.075 (density, lb/ft&#179;)</text>
  <text x="150" y="260" fill={C.muted} font-family={FONT} font-size="11">Used for total heat against enthalpy (BTU/lb of dry air).</text>

  <text x="360" y="302" text-anchor="middle" fill={C.muted} font-family={FONT} font-size="11">All three assume standard air: 0.075 lb/ft&#179; at sea level, about 70&#176;F.</text>
</svg>
